Is anyone surprised I got a shirtless photo this weekend? 🤷🏾‍♂️ Well what’s the point of having these muscles if you aren’t going to put them to good use? #FBF: Three weeks ago, I had the pleasure of meeting @secretarypete at the annual @cgiuniversity conference. (@clintonglobal) It was the first night of the event and right before the Secretary hit the stage to share his message to the leaders of tomorrow. 

Now if you go into the way back machine during the 2020 primary season, you may find me espousing support for someone other than his historic candidacy. It even became a running joke amongst my friends who were paying attention. However, I can’t explain how much it does to actually meet someone. You can hear them in their own words and talk about what you have in common. Mayor Pete made me a true believer in him that night. I can tell that his heart is sincere and he truly puts his all into everything that he does whether it be leading South Bend Indiana, troops in Afghanistan, or now the US Department of Transportation. This guy is the real deal. Smart, caring, and such a wonderful husband & father. 

Meeting with the secretary certainly was an honor. We got to talk as peers about the issues pressing our world today. We’re both 80s babies. We still want the bright world we were promised. Pete’s constant dunking on FoxNews helps us get there a little sooner. It was an honor and I look forward to our next get together. Maybe he’ll be president and I’ll be the cabinet member. 🇺🇸

PS: We spoke at length about being musicians. We both have Gershwin’s “Rhapsody in Blue” as our signature pieces. However, Pete plays the full concert orchestral version. I play the two page dumbed down arrangement 😅🎹💙

The boyhood dream

Ok, I know I spammed my stories with all the hype from #WrestleMania. I get it if you scrolled by but let me explain.

In 2000, a 12 year old Brandon stood outside WrestleMania in Anaheim hoping to get a ticket and see his hero, @therock. That didn’t happen. To be on the doorstep of the biggest event of your young life and NOT GO IN? That honestly became a metaphor for my life. Always had the passion, always was right there but it was never MY TIME. These past two nights were about fulfilling a promise to that Little Brandon still inside me. We did it buddy!! 
WE WERE AT WRESTLEMANIA! 🥹😭

My dream was to be there with title belts in hand at the Showcase of the Immortals. These belts are more than adult-size toys to me. I call them Vulky & Vixy. They represent the Dark 🖤 & Fairy 💖 types. That’s me.  Equal parts sinister & sincere. To have these on my shoulders while being there meant so much. This was one bucket list item down. 
Now… I can do all the rest ☝🏾

#DarkVictoryBC #WrestleMania39 #Undisputed #UndisputedWWEUniversialChampion #WWE #Wrestling #BoyhoodDream #DreamsDoComeTrue #NeverGiveUp

Thank you to @aldophotog for reminding us that Black History is year round. Always giving us a wonderful historical perspective. Here, I’m honored to portray Narmer. Many scholars consider him the unifier of Egypt and founder of the First Dynasty, and in turn the first non-mythical king of a unified Egypt. This seems very appropriate for me. A healer and uniter. Definitely needed in times like this.
